main event: A witness observed a star-like object traveling slowly from the North-East sky to the West in Green, Kentucky on March 13, 1967.
interesting points: The object hovered for several minutes before disappearing completely., The witness remarked that the object was brighter than the stars and had a white center with lighter blue edges., An unidentified aircraft was seen approaching the object just before the lights went out., The witness heard a light humming sound associated with the object., The official conclusion of the report was that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: Mrs. Georgia Elliot, observed the object with her daughter.
